37:00"}}, "350": {"text": "When will I-15 reopen? Officer-involved shooting closes Interstate 15 between Murray and South Salt Lake, Utah. The Utah Department of Transportation said the road was expected to reopen around 10 p.m. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/us-news/when-will-i-15-reopen-officer-involved-shooting-closes-interstate-15-between-murray-and-south-salt-lake-utah-101774657865202.html", "title": "When will I-15 reopen? Officer-involved shooting closes Interstate 15 between Murray and South Salt Lake, Utah", "description": "The Utah Department of Transportation said the road was expected to reopen around 10 p.m.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:36:58"}}, "351": {"text": "Notre Dame's unlikely run to the Elite Eight started with offseason dedication to Niele Ivey. \"To be ... still dancing, it's honestly a blessing.\" ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7152898/2026/03/27/notre-dames-elite-eight-niele-ivey/", "title": "Notre Dame's unlikely run to the Elite Eight started with offseason dedication to Niele Ivey", "description": "\"To be ... still dancing, it's honestly a blessing.\"", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:36:36"}}, "352": {"text": "North Platte business owner launches fencing donation drive for wildfire-affected ranches. North Platte business owner launches fencing donation drive for wildfire-affected ranches ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.knopnews2.com/2026/03/28/north-platte-business-owner-launches-fencing-donation-drive-wildfire-affected-ranches/", "title": "North Platte business owner launches fencing donation drive for wildfire-affected ranches", "description": "North Platte business owner launches fencing donation drive for wildfire-affected ranches", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:36:33"}}, "353": {"text": "EUR/USD Forex Signal 26/03: Bearish Flag Pattern Points To A. (MENAFN - Daily Forex) Bearish viewEURUSD Chart by TradingView Sell the EUR/USD pair and set a take-profit at 1.1412 Add a stop-loss at 1.1650. Timeline: 1-2 days. Bullish view Buy the EUR/USD ... ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://menafn.com/1110911831/EURUSD-Forex-Signal-2603-Bearish-Flag-Pattern-Points-To-A", "title": "EUR/USD Forex Signal 26/03: Bearish Flag Pattern Points To A", "description": "(MENAFN - Daily Forex) Bearish viewEURUSD Chart by TradingView Sell the EUR/USD pair and set a take-profit at 1.1412 Add a stop-loss at 1.1650. Timeline: 1-2 days. Bullish view Buy the EUR/USD ...", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:35:51"}}, "354": {"text": "Back to the Future star James Tolkan dead at 94: Beloved actor also commanded Tom Cruise in Top Gun. Tolkan featured in Robert Zemeckis' original 1985 Back to the Future movie as Hill Valley High School chief Mr. Strickland, who is given to denouncing 'slackers.' ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-15686653/back-future-star-james-tolkan-dead-94-character-actor-tom-cruise-gun.html", "title": "Back to the Future star James Tolkan dead at 94: Beloved actor also commanded Tom Cruise in Top Gun", "description": "Tolkan featured in Robert Zemeckis' original 1985 Back to the Future movie as Hill Valley High School chief Mr. Strickland, who is given to denouncing 'slackers.'", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:35:46"}}, "355": {"text": "'Another 3,554 targets left': Trump says war with Iran is 'not over yet'. US special envoy Steve Witkoff said Friday he believes Iran will hold talks with Washington 'this week,' as President Donald Trump reiterated his claims that Tehran wants to make a deal ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.firstpost.com/world/another-3554-targets-left-trump-says-war-with-iran-is-not-over-yet-13993935.html", "title": "'Another 3,554 targets left': Trump says war with Iran is 'not over yet'", "description": "US special envoy Steve Witkoff said Friday he believes Iran will hold talks with Washington 'this week,' as President Donald Trump reiterated his claims that Tehran wants to make a deal", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:35:39"}}, "356": {"text": "Downtown Las Vegas casino owners default on $82.5M loan, property in receivership. The receivership is well underway and the receiver has already begun a formal effort to sell the hotel-casino. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.reviewjournal.com/business/casinos-gaming/downtown-las-vegas-casino-owners-default-on-82-5m-loan-property-in-receivership-3730613/", "title": "Downtown Las Vegas casino owners default on $82.5M loan, property in receivership", "description": "The receivership is well underway and the receiver has already begun a formal effort to sell the hotel-casino.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:35:29"}}, "357": {"text": "Tourism serves as bridge connecting cultures and people between Viet Nam and Japan. In 2025, the number of Japanese visitors to Viet Nam reached 814,000, up 14.4% compared to 2024. Meanwhile, the number of Vietnamese visitors to Japan reached 678,500, up 9.2% year-on-year. Thus, two-way tourist flows have shown recovery and growth, although the market has not yet fully returned to pre-2019 levels.", "metadata": {"source": "https://en.nhandan.vn/tourism-serves-as-bridge-connecting-cultures-and-people-between-viet-nam-and-japan-post160468.html", "title": "Tourism serves as bridge connecting cultures and people between Viet Nam and Japan", "description": "In 2025, the number of Japanese visitors to Viet Nam reached 814,000, up 14.4% compared to 2024. Meanwhile, the number of Vietnamese visitors to Japan reached 678,500, up 9.2% year-on-year. Thus, two-way tourist flows have shown recovery and growth, although the market has not yet fully returned to pre-2019 levels. Viet Nam\u2013Japan cooperation advances green growth and climate resilience Viet Nam values Japan as key strategic partner: Party official Viet Nam, Japan expand cooperation in various fields", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:35:23"}}, "358": {"text": "has not yet fully returned to pre-2019 levels. Viet Nam\u2013Japan cooperation advances green growth and climate resilience Viet Nam values Japan as key strategic partner: Party official Viet Nam, Japan expand cooperation in various fields ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://en.nhandan.vn/tourism-serves-as-bridge-connecting-cultures-and-people-between-viet-nam-and-japan-post160468.html", "title": "Tourism serves as bridge connecting cultures and people between Viet Nam and Japan", "description": "In 2025, the number of Japanese visitors to Viet Nam reached 814,000, up 14.4% compared to 2024. Meanwhile, the number of Vietnamese visitors to Japan reached 678,500, up 9.2% year-on-year. Thus, two-way tourist flows have shown recovery and growth, although the market has not yet fully returned to pre-2019 levels. Viet Nam\u2013Japan cooperation advances green growth and climate resilience Viet Nam values Japan as key strategic partner: Party official Viet Nam, Japan expand cooperation in various fields", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:35:23"}}, "359": {"text": "Gloucester girls lax drops season opener at Essex Tech. DANVERS \u2014 The start of the spring sports season is upon us. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.gloucestertimes.com/sports/gloucester-girls-lax-drops-season-opener-at-essex-tech/article_270cac06-8daa-48c7-b831-7e8d55ebc8bd.html", "title": "Gloucester girls lax drops season opener at Essex Tech", "description": "DANVERS \u2014 The start of the spring sports season is upon us.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 00:35:00"}}, "360": {"text": "Australians in a series of isolated coastal towns battered by a destructive cyclone are emerging from their homes to assess the damage. Australians in a series of isolated coastal towns battered by a destructive cyclone are emerging from their homes to assess the damage ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://home.nzcity.co.nz/news/article.aspx?id=442777", "title": "Australians in a series of isolated coastal towns battered by a destructive cyclone are emerging from their homes to assess the damage", "description": "Australians in a series of isolated coastal towns battered by a destructive cyclone are emerging from their homes to assess the damage", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:59"}}, "361": {"text": "White Marsh bakery sees surge in business after going viral on social media. A woman-owned bakery in White Marsh is experiencing a surge in business after the owner's honest plea on Facebook went viral. Yummery, located on Philadelphia Road for almost 12 years, serves cookies, wedding cakes, cupcakes and much more. Despite being open for over a decade, owner Christi Weker said the bakery recently", "metadata": {"source": "https://ca.news.yahoo.com/white-marsh-bakery-sees-surge-031649292.html", "title": "White Marsh bakery sees surge in business after going viral on social media", "description": "A woman-owned bakery in White Marsh is experiencing a surge in business after the owner's honest plea on Facebook went viral. Yummery, located on Philadelphia Road for almost 12 years, serves cookies, wedding cakes, cupcakes and much more. Despite being open for over a decade, owner Christi Weker said the bakery recently struggled to bring in customers, seeing only four people on one particularly slow day. \"We opened the doors, and I expected to have lines around the building and it just never happened. We were all just standing around waiting to be discovered,\" Weker said.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:49"}}, "362": {"text": "owner Christi Weker said the bakery recently struggled to bring in customers, seeing only four people on one particularly slow day. \"We opened the doors, and I expected to have lines around the building and it just never happened. We were all just standing around waiting to be discovered,\" Weker said. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://ca.news.yahoo.com/white-marsh-bakery-sees-surge-031649292.html", "title": "White Marsh bakery sees surge in business after going viral on social media", "description": "A woman-owned bakery in White Marsh is experiencing a surge in business after the owner's honest plea on Facebook went viral. Yummery, located on Philadelphia Road for almost 12 years, serves cookies, wedding cakes, cupcakes and much more. Despite being open for over a decade, owner Christi Weker said the bakery recently struggled to bring in customers, seeing only four people on one particularly slow day. \"We opened the doors, and I expected to have lines around the building and it just never happened. We were all just standing around waiting to be discovered,\" Weker said.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:49"}}, "363": {"text": "China boycotts top AI conference after ban on papers from US-sanctioned entities. China\u2019s largest federation for science and technology professionals on Friday announced a boycott of a top artificial intelligence conference after the California-based foundation that runs the gathering stopped accepting submissions from entities under U.S. sanctions. The Conference on Neural Information Processing", "metadata": {"source": "https://telecomlive.in/web/2026/03/28/china-boycotts-top-ai-conference-after-ban-on-papers-from-us-sanctioned-entities/", "title": "China boycotts top AI conference after ban on papers from US-sanctioned entities", "description": "China\u2019s largest federation for science and technology professionals on Friday announced a boycott of a top artificial intelligence conference after the California-based foundation that runs the gathering stopped accepting submissions from entities under U.S. sanctions. The Conference on Neural Information Processing Systems, known as NeurIPS, announced earlier this week a policy change that effectively banned entities like Chinese \u200ctech companies \u2060Huawei and \u2060SMIC under U.S. sanctions from submitting papers.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:19"}}, "364": {"text": "The Conference on Neural Information Processing Systems, known as NeurIPS, announced earlier this week a policy change that effectively banned entities like Chinese \u200ctech companies \u2060Huawei and \u2060SMIC under U.S. sanctions from submitting papers. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://telecomlive.in/web/2026/03/28/china-boycotts-top-ai-conference-after-ban-on-papers-from-us-sanctioned-entities/", "title": "China boycotts top AI conference after ban on papers from US-sanctioned entities", "description": "China\u2019s largest federation for science and technology professionals on Friday announced a boycott of a top artificial intelligence conference after the California-based foundation that runs the gathering stopped accepting submissions from entities under U.S. sanctions. The Conference on Neural Information Processing Systems, known as NeurIPS, announced earlier this week a policy change that effectively banned entities like Chinese \u200ctech companies \u2060Huawei and \u2060SMIC under U.S. sanctions from submitting papers.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:19"}}, "365": {"text": "ATS Launches in the U.S. at ATP Conference in New Orleans. Image: https://www.abnewswire.com/upload/2026/03/25f440997145ea7170005d14a893640e.jpg New Orleans, Louisiana, USA - ATA Talent Services (ATS) [https://www.atstests.com/] made its debut in the U.S. at the 2026 ATP Conference in New Orleans, showcasing its scalable and technology-based testing and assessment solutions. The event marked ATS's", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.openpr.com/news/4444379/ats-launches-in-the-u-s-at-atp-conference-in-new-orleans", "title": "ATS Launches in the U.S. at ATP Conference in New Orleans", "description": "Image: https://www.abnewswire.com/upload/2026/03/25f440997145ea7170005d14a893640e.jpg New Orleans, Louisiana, USA - ATA Talent Services (ATS) [https://www.atstests.com/] made its debut in the U.S. at the 2026 ATP Conference in New Orleans, showcasing its scalable and technology-based testing and assessment solutions. The event marked ATS's first public", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:03"}}, "366": {"text": "and assessment solutions. The event marked ATS's first public ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.openpr.com/news/4444379/ats-launches-in-the-u-s-at-atp-conference-in-new-orleans", "title": "ATS Launches in the U.S. at ATP Conference in New Orleans", "description": "Image: https://www.abnewswire.com/upload/2026/03/25f440997145ea7170005d14a893640e.jpg New Orleans, Louisiana, USA - ATA Talent Services (ATS) [https://www.atstests.com/] made its debut in the U.S. at the 2026 ATP Conference in New Orleans, showcasing its scalable and technology-based testing and assessment solutions. The event marked ATS's first public", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:03"}}, "367": {"text": "I need help in remembering a tv miniseries or tv movie. What I remember about it is that it is approximately a Victorian era movie or miniseries. The show aired anywhere from the late 70's to late 80's. In the show, it involves an older sister or single mother and two younger children who are taken in by a compassionate wealthy young gentleman, possibly an aristocrat. He tries to raise the", "metadata": {"source": "https://freerepublic.com/focus/f-chat/4372550/posts", "title": "I need help in remembering a tv miniseries or tv movie", "description": "What I remember about it is that it is approximately a Victorian era movie or miniseries. The show aired anywhere from the late 70's to late 80's. In the show, it involves an older sister or single mother and two younger children who are taken in by a compassionate wealthy young gentleman, possibly an aristocrat. He tries to raise the children to be fit for his level of society, but the young man becomes resentful of him and ends up stabbing him in the leg when the young man reveals that he is now broke because of bad investments. I...", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:03"}}, "368": {"text": "possibly an aristocrat. He tries to raise the children to be fit for his level of society, but the young man becomes resentful of him and ends up stabbing him in the leg when the young man reveals that he is now broke because of bad investments. I... ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://freerepublic.com/focus/f-chat/4372550/posts", "title": "I need help in remembering a tv miniseries or tv movie", "description": "What I remember about it is that it is approximately a Victorian era movie or miniseries. The show aired anywhere from the late 70's to late 80's. In the show, it involves an older sister or single mother and two younger children who are taken in by a compassionate wealthy young gentleman, possibly an aristocrat. He tries to raise the children to be fit for his level of society, but the young man becomes resentful of him and ends up stabbing him in the leg when the young man reveals that he is now broke because of bad investments. I...", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:16:03"}}, "369": {"text": "Middle school students from Lexington, Massachusetts escape bus fire on New Hampshire highway. A tour bus carrying dozens of middle school students from Lexington, Massachusetts caught fire on I-93 in Woodstock, New Hampshire on Friday night. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.cbsnews.com/boston/news/lexington-middle-school-students-bus-fire-new-hampshire/", "title": "Middle school students from Lexington, Massachusetts escape bus fire on New Hampshire highway", "description": "A tour bus carrying dozens of middle school students from Lexington, Massachusetts caught fire on I-93 in Woodstock, New Hampshire on Friday night.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:15:13"}}, "370": {"text": "Expands Moving Operations in Raleigh, Focusing on White Glove Delivery and Commercial Moving Services at New Location. Just another WordPress site ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://norfolkdailynews.com/online_features/press_releases/expands-moving-operations-in-raleigh-focusing-on-white-glove-delivery-and-commercial-moving-services-at/article_8c94a9b4-2e13-5a01-a105-ccd4395b60bc.html", "title": "Expands Moving Operations in Raleigh, Focusing on White Glove Delivery and Commercial Moving Services at New Location", "description": "Just another WordPress site", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:15:02"}}, "371": {"text": "Popular chocolatier, running company and four more crash into administration. Several companies have went into administration recently, including a vape giant and a photo studio too. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/life/2186918/uk-companies-administration-news", "title": "Popular chocolatier, running company and four more crash into administration", "description": "Several companies have went into administration recently, including a vape giant and a photo studio too.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:15:00"}}, "372": {"text": "Popular chocolate maker, running company and four more plunge into administration. A chocolate maker, a bike manufacturer and a vape distributor are among the companies that have recently entered administration. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/popular-chocolate-maker-running-company-36927328", "title": "Popular chocolate maker, running company and four more plunge into administration", "description": "A chocolate maker, a bike manufacturer and a vape distributor are among the companies that have recently entered administration.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:15:00"}}, "373": {"text": "Duck confit for $18++: Where to get affordable French food in Singapore. Les Ducs and Bouillon Gavroche are bringing the taste of Parisian bouillons to Singapore. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.straitstimes.com/life/food/duck-confit-for-18-where-to-get-affordable-french-food", "title": "Duck confit for $18++: Where to get affordable French food in Singapore", "description": "Les Ducs and Bouillon Gavroche are bringing the taste of Parisian bouillons to Singapore.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:15:00"}}, "374": {"text": "US envoy hopeful on Iran talks as strikes target nuclear facilities. TEHRAN (AFP) : US President Donald Trump\u2019s special envoy Steve Witkoff said Friday (Mar 27) he believes Iran will hold talks with Washington \u201cthis week\u201d to end the month-long war, as US-Israeli strikes hit two Iranian nuclear facilities. Iran threatened retaliation against industrial sites in the region, with no clear end to the", "metadata": {"source": "https://thefrontierpost.com/us-envoy-hopeful-on-iran-talks-as-strikes-target-nuclear-facilities/", "title": "US envoy hopeful on Iran talks as strikes target nuclear facilities", "description": "TEHRAN (AFP) : US President Donald Trump\u2019s special envoy Steve Witkoff said Friday (Mar 27) he believes Iran will hold talks with Washington \u201cthis week\u201d to end the month-long war, as US-Israeli strikes hit two Iranian nuclear facilities. Iran threatened retaliation against industrial sites in the region, with no clear end to the conflict in [...]", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:28:23"}}, "375": {"text": "sites in the region, with no clear end to the conflict in [...] ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://thefrontierpost.com/us-envoy-hopeful-on-iran-talks-as-strikes-target-nuclear-facilities/", "title": "US envoy hopeful on Iran talks as strikes target nuclear facilities", "description": "TEHRAN (AFP) : US President Donald Trump\u2019s special envoy Steve Witkoff said Friday (Mar 27) he believes Iran will hold talks with Washington \u201cthis week\u201d to end the month-long war, as US-Israeli strikes hit two Iranian nuclear facilities. Iran threatened retaliation against industrial sites in the region, with no clear end to the conflict in [...]", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:28:23"}}, "376": {"text": "Massive bird flu hits three Koshi districts. By Hari Prasad Koirala,Urlabari, Mar. 28: The recent outbreak of bird flu in Jhapa, Morang, and Sunsari districts over t... ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://risingnepaldaily.com/news/77869", "title": "Massive bird flu hits three Koshi districts", "description": "By Hari Prasad Koirala,Urlabari, Mar. 28: The recent outbreak of bird flu in Jhapa, Morang, and Sunsari districts over t...", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:28:18"}}, "377": {"text": "New Beauty Trends Show How Hairline, Brow and Lash Procedures Are Redefining Confidence for Women. Experts highlight growing demand for subtle, long-lasting enhancements that support natural beauty and self-expression 27 March, 2026 - United Kingdom - Beauty and medical professionals across the United Kingdom are observing a growing shift in how women approach personal aesthetics, with ONLY", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.openpr.com/news/4444392/new-beauty-trends-show-how-hairline-brow-and-lash-procedures", "title": "New Beauty Trends Show How Hairline, Brow and Lash Procedures Are Redefining Confidence for Women", "description": "Experts highlight growing demand for subtle, long-lasting enhancements that support natural beauty and self-expression 27 March, 2026 - United Kingdom - Beauty and medical professionals across the United Kingdom are observing a growing shift in how women approach personal aesthetics, with", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:28:05"}}, "378": {"text": "how women approach personal aesthetics, with ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.openpr.com/news/4444392/new-beauty-trends-show-how-hairline-brow-and-lash-procedures", "title": "New Beauty Trends Show How Hairline, Brow and Lash Procedures Are Redefining Confidence for Women", "description": "Experts highlight growing demand for subtle, long-lasting enhancements that support natural beauty and self-expression 27 March, 2026 - United Kingdom - Beauty and medical professionals across the United Kingdom are observing a growing shift in how women approach personal aesthetics, with", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:28:05"}}, "379": {"text": "Oriental Insurance Crosses \u20b920,000 Crore Gross Premium In FY 2025-26. State-owned Oriental Insurance Company has achieved a major milestone by surpassing Rs 20,000 crore in gross premium for FY 2025-26, the Finance Ministry announced. Driven by strong performance in the Group Personal Accident, Health, Fire, and Motor segments, the growth reflects rising trust in public-sector insurers. OICL", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.freepressjournal.in/business/oriental-insurance-crosses-20000-crore-gross-premium-in-fy-2025-26", "title": "Oriental Insurance Crosses \u20b920,000 Crore Gross Premium In FY 2025-26", "description": "State-owned Oriental Insurance Company has achieved a major milestone by surpassing Rs 20,000 crore in gross premium for FY 2025-26, the Finance Ministry announced. Driven by strong performance in the Group Personal Accident, Health, Fire, and Motor segments, the growth reflects rising trust in public-sector insurers. OICL continues to expand its product portfolio with innovative offerings.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:27:30"}}, "380": {"text": "rising trust in public-sector insurers. OICL continues to expand its product portfolio with innovative offerings. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.freepressjournal.in/business/oriental-insurance-crosses-20000-crore-gross-premium-in-fy-2025-26", "title": "Oriental Insurance Crosses \u20b920,000 Crore Gross Premium In FY 2025-26", "description": "State-owned Oriental Insurance Company has achieved a major milestone by surpassing Rs 20,000 crore in gross premium for FY 2025-26, the Finance Ministry announced. Driven by strong performance in the Group Personal Accident, Health, Fire, and Motor segments, the growth reflects rising trust in public-sector insurers. OICL continues to expand its product portfolio with innovative offerings.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:27:30"}}, "381": {"text": "Saskatoon\u2019s Gather Local Market welcomes Rebellion as its newest anchor tenant. Rebellion was started in Regina by Mark Heise and his business partners, where they have their own brewery. ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://globalnews.ca/news/11749746/gather-local-market-welcomes-rebellion-newest-anchor-tenant/", "title": "Saskatoon\u2019s Gather Local Market welcomes Rebellion as its newest anchor tenant", "description": "Rebellion was started in Regina by Mark Heise and his business partners, where they have their own brewery.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:26:57"}}, "382": {"text": "Sign on the Dotted Line: Keeping Security and Sustainability in Focus for W&W Informatik Group\u2019s Mobile Sales Force. With a history stretching back to 1828, and a list of \u2018firsts\u2019 including being the debut German pension insurance and building society, the 16 companies that make up Germany\u2019s Wu\u0308stenrot & Wu\u0308rttembergische (W&W) Informatik Group delivers everything from investment products to risk", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.csr-company.com/node/11545", "title": "Sign on the Dotted Line: Keeping Security and Sustainability in Focus for W&W Informatik Group\u2019s Mobile Sales Force", "description": "With a history stretching back to 1828, and a list of \u2018firsts\u2019 including being the debut German pension insurance and building society, the 16 companies that make up Germany\u2019s Wu\u0308stenrot & Wu\u0308rttembergische (W&W) Informatik Group delivers everything from investment products to risk protection to 6.5 million customers. W&W Informatik Group relies on a highly connected mobile sales force of 8,000 people spread across 2,500 service centers and offices. With contracts increasingly being signed digitally, W&W needed a new device and services strategy to ensure its team had the support required to bring new customers on board. For W&W\u2019s front-line salespeople, it was essential for the devices to be fast and reliable and secure for processing customer data, with security and sustainability also critical business considerations. W&W Informatik Group is committed to a sustainability strategy focused on reducing the company\u2019s carbon footprint and lessening the environmental impact of its operations. Therefore, it was crucial that the devices used by its mobile sales force were shipped, built and recycled in a way that aligned with W&W\u2019s sustainability strategy. Uli Linko, Head of Client System Technology, at the group\u2019s technology arm W&W Informatik GmbH, said, \u201cWe are always looking for ways to further improve data protection and device security. And with AI-supported tools being developed, we needed to equip our sales force with powerful devices that can handle larger amounts of data and more demanding workloads.\u201d W&W had been using Lenovo ThinkPad laptops at its head office for many years and relying on Lenovo server infrastructure. So the team spoke to Lenovo to find the right approach, settling on Lenovo\u2019s \u2018two-in-one\u2019 ThinkPad X13 Yoga Gen 4 laptops, powerful machines which can switch from a laptop mode with a traditional keyboard, to a \u2018tablet mode\u2019 where users can write on screen, perfect for when customers need to sign contracts. To help W&W make its decision, Lenovo was able to provide rapid access to different test devices through its local European lab in Bratislava. Across the lifecycle W&W was looking for more than just devices. For mobile teams dealing with financial products, it was key that the solution could deliver high levels of security, alongside the flexibility for salespeople to work safely from anywhere. The ThinkPad\u2019s touchscreens and built-in styluses meant that W&W could keep costs down and reduce the need to carry additional external hardware. Lenovo also helped W&W find a solution that helped its salespeople stay connected on the go, including eSIM functionality for mobile connectivity and remote management of future network upgrades. For additional security, W&W also opted for a Near Field Communication (NFC) reader which could be used to verify customers using ID cards, or for staff to log in using multi-factor authentication. With the devices rolling out to a first wave of 1,400 users with Lenovo\u2019s partner Bechtle, W&W\u2019s experts opted for Lenovo ThinkShield Remote Supervisor Password (RSVP) service, which enables remote management of passwords on a large scale. Linko said, \u201cLenovo understands what is important for us, proactively suggesting features like the new password service to increase device security. The eSIM functionality means we will no longer need to deal with faulty SIM cards and we will be able to change connectivity providers much more easily in the future.\u201d Delivering sustainably Lenovo also considered sustainability impact from shipping through to end-of-life. W&W opted for Lenovo\u2019s Maersk ECO Delivery for many of the devices, using second-generation biofuels to reduce shipping CO2 emissions by more than 80% . The ThinkPad laptops also offer real-time performance reports via Lenovo Device Intelligence (LDI) Plus, an AI-powered Software as a Service (SaaS) PC health management tool which provides detailed device analytics and real-time utilization reports to extend their life. These measures were supplemented by Lenovo CO2 Offset Services , allowing W&W to purchase carbon credits with each device, which support a range of United Nations and Gold Standard\u00ae vetted climate action projects around the world. In addition, Lenovo\u2019s Asset Recovery Services provide secure, documented disposal and recycling of IT hardware when it has reached the end of its useful life. John Stamer, Vice President & General Manager, Global Product Services at Lenovo said : \u201c By optimizing the shipment of ThinkPad devices and collaborating closely with our lab in Bratislava to minimize road miles for testing, our team supported W&W in significantly reducing the carbon footprint of their devices and services. Additionally, Lenovo Device Intelligence Plus enhanced the company\u2019s visibility into device usage, empowering W&W to make informed decisions and drive operational efficiency.\u201d Linko said, \u201cAt our head office, we often use ThinkPad laptops for as long as eight years without issues. With LDI Plus, we can better understand what features are important for our teams and where the bottlenecks are. Using the new metrics and data, we can proactively optimize device configurations and make much better-informed decisions about upgrades and configurations.\u201d Future-ready results The W&W team have high standards for their hardware, and even the most exacting users have been happy with the Lenovo devices. The ThinkPad machines are also ready for future upgrades to NFC-based security, AI workloads and for the move to Windows 11. Lenovo\u2019s software has enabled W&W to manage laptops more intelligently, enabling managers to see how teams are actually using them, offering insights which will be useful for choosing future upgrades. Linko said that the initial rollout has been met with a \u2018very positive\u2019 reaction. He added, \u2018The high-spec configuration gives everyone an impressive performance boost across many complex business applications, increasing staff productivity and satisfaction. Together with Lenovo, we have created a sustainable, future-focused, AI-ready workhorse for our distributed salesforce.\u201d LENOVO and ThinkPad are trademarks of Lenovo. All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners. \u00a92026 Lenovo Learn more about Lenovo\u2019s work with W&W Informatik Learn more about Lenovo CO2 Offset Services Only for Cyprus section No", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:26:12"}}, "383": {"text": "everything from investment products to risk protection to 6.5 million customers. W&W Informatik Group relies on a highly connected mobile sales force of 8,000 people spread across 2,500 service centers and offices. With contracts increasingly being signed digitally, W&W needed a new device and services strategy to ensure its team had the support required to bring new customers on board. For W&W\u2019s", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.csr-company.com/node/11545", "title": "Sign on the Dotted Line: Keeping Security and Sustainability in Focus for W&W Informatik Group\u2019s Mobile Sales Force", "description": "With a history stretching back to 1828, and a list of \u2018firsts\u2019 including being the debut German pension insurance and building society, the 16 companies that make up Germany\u2019s Wu\u0308stenrot & Wu\u0308rttembergische (W&W) Informatik Group delivers everything from investment products to risk protection to 6.5 million customers. W&W Informatik Group relies on a highly connected mobile sales force of 8,000 people spread across 2,500 service centers and offices. With contracts increasingly being signed digitally, W&W needed a new device and services strategy to ensure its team had the support required to bring new customers on board. For W&W\u2019s front-line salespeople, it was essential for the devices to be fast and reliable and secure for processing customer data, with security and sustainability also critical business considerations. W&W Informatik Group is committed to a sustainability strategy focused on reducing the company\u2019s carbon footprint and lessening the environmental impact of its operations. Therefore, it was crucial that the devices used by its mobile sales force were shipped, built and recycled in a way that aligned with W&W\u2019s sustainability strategy. Uli Linko, Head of Client System Technology, at the group\u2019s technology arm W&W Informatik GmbH, said, \u201cWe are always looking for ways to further improve data protection and device security. And with AI-supported tools being developed, we needed to equip our sales force with powerful devices that can handle larger amounts of data and more demanding workloads.\u201d W&W had been using Lenovo ThinkPad laptops at its head office for many years and relying on Lenovo server infrastructure. So the team spoke to Lenovo to find the right approach, settling on Lenovo\u2019s \u2018two-in-one\u2019 ThinkPad X13 Yoga Gen 4 laptops, powerful machines which can switch from a laptop mode with a traditional keyboard, to a \u2018tablet mode\u2019 where users can write on screen, perfect for when customers need to sign contracts. To help W&W make its decision, Lenovo was able to provide rapid access to different test devices through its local European lab in Bratislava. Across the lifecycle W&W was looking for more than just devices. For mobile teams dealing with financial products, it was key that the solution could deliver high levels of security, alongside the flexibility for salespeople to work safely from anywhere. The ThinkPad\u2019s touchscreens and built-in styluses meant that W&W could keep costs down and reduce the need to carry additional external hardware. Lenovo also helped W&W find a solution that helped its salespeople stay connected on the go, including eSIM functionality for mobile connectivity and remote management of future network upgrades. For additional security, W&W also opted for a Near Field Communication (NFC) reader which could be used to verify customers using ID cards, or for staff to log in using multi-factor authentication. With the devices rolling out to a first wave of 1,400 users with Lenovo\u2019s partner Bechtle, W&W\u2019s experts opted for Lenovo ThinkShield Remote Supervisor Password (RSVP) service, which enables remote management of passwords on a large scale. Linko said, \u201cLenovo understands what is important for us, proactively suggesting features like the new password service to increase device security. The eSIM functionality means we will no longer need to deal with faulty SIM cards and we will be able to change connectivity providers much more easily in the future.\u201d Delivering sustainably Lenovo also considered sustainability impact from shipping through to end-of-life. W&W opted for Lenovo\u2019s Maersk ECO Delivery for many of the devices, using second-generation biofuels to reduce shipping CO2 emissions by more than 80% . The ThinkPad laptops also offer real-time performance reports via Lenovo Device Intelligence (LDI) Plus, an AI-powered Software as a Service (SaaS) PC health management tool which provides detailed device analytics and real-time utilization reports to extend their life. These measures were supplemented by Lenovo CO2 Offset Services , allowing W&W to purchase carbon credits with each device, which support a range of United Nations and Gold Standard\u00ae vetted climate action projects around the world. In addition, Lenovo\u2019s Asset Recovery Services provide secure, documented disposal and recycling of IT hardware when it has reached the end of its useful life. John Stamer, Vice President & General Manager, Global Product Services at Lenovo said : \u201c By optimizing the shipment of ThinkPad devices and collaborating closely with our lab in Bratislava to minimize road miles for testing, our team supported W&W in significantly reducing the carbon footprint of their devices and services. Additionally, Lenovo Device Intelligence Plus enhanced the company\u2019s visibility into device usage, empowering W&W to make informed decisions and drive operational efficiency.\u201d Linko said, \u201cAt our head office, we often use ThinkPad laptops for as long as eight years without issues. With LDI Plus, we can better understand what features are important for our teams and where the bottlenecks are. Using the new metrics and data, we can proactively optimize device configurations and make much better-informed decisions about upgrades and configurations.\u201d Future-ready results The W&W team have high standards for their hardware, and even the most exacting users have been happy with the Lenovo devices. The ThinkPad machines are also ready for future upgrades to NFC-based security, AI workloads and for the move to Windows 11. Lenovo\u2019s software has enabled W&W to manage laptops more intelligently, enabling managers to see how teams are actually using them, offering insights which will be useful for choosing future upgrades. Linko said that the initial rollout has been met with a \u2018very positive\u2019 reaction. He added, \u2018The high-spec configuration gives everyone an impressive performance boost across many complex business applications, increasing staff productivity and satisfaction. Together with Lenovo, we have created a sustainable, future-focused, AI-ready workhorse for our distributed salesforce.\u201d LENOVO and ThinkPad are trademarks of Lenovo. All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners. \u00a92026 Lenovo Learn more about Lenovo\u2019s work with W&W Informatik Learn more about Lenovo CO2 Offset Services Only for Cyprus section No", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:26:12"}}, "384": {"text": "to bring new customers on board. For W&W\u2019s front-line salespeople, it was essential for the devices to be fast and reliable and secure for processing customer data, with security and sustainability also critical business considerations. W&W Informatik Group is committed to a sustainability strategy focused on reducing the company\u2019s carbon footprint and lessening the environmental impact of its", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.csr-company.com/node/11545", "title": "Sign on the Dotted Line: Keeping Security and Sustainability in Focus for W&W Informatik Group\u2019s Mobile Sales Force", "description": "With a history stretching back to 1828, and a list of \u2018firsts\u2019 including being the debut German pension insurance and building society, the 16 companies that make up Germany\u2019s Wu\u0308stenrot & Wu\u0308rttembergische (W&W) Informatik Group delivers everything from investment products to risk protection to 6.5 million customers. W&W Informatik Group relies on a highly connected mobile sales force of 8,000 people spread across 2,500 service centers and offices. With contracts increasingly being signed digitally, W&W needed a new device and services strategy to ensure its team had the support required to bring new customers on board. For W&W\u2019s front-line salespeople, it was essential for the devices to be fast and reliable and secure for processing customer data, with security and sustainability also critical business considerations. W&W Informatik Group is committed to a sustainability strategy focused on reducing the company\u2019s carbon footprint and lessening the environmental impact of its operations. Therefore, it was crucial that the devices used by its mobile sales force were shipped, built and recycled in a way that aligned with W&W\u2019s sustainability strategy. Uli Linko, Head of Client System Technology, at the group\u2019s technology arm W&W Informatik GmbH, said, \u201cWe are always looking for ways to further improve data protection and device security. And with AI-supported tools being developed, we needed to equip our sales force with powerful devices that can handle larger amounts of data and more demanding workloads.\u201d W&W had been using Lenovo ThinkPad laptops at its head office for many years and relying on Lenovo server infrastructure. So the team spoke to Lenovo to find the right approach, settling on Lenovo\u2019s \u2018two-in-one\u2019 ThinkPad X13 Yoga Gen 4 laptops, powerful machines which can switch from a laptop mode with a traditional keyboard, to a \u2018tablet mode\u2019 where users can write on screen, perfect for when customers need to sign contracts. To help W&W make its decision, Lenovo was able to provide rapid access to different test devices through its local European lab in Bratislava. Across the lifecycle W&W was looking for more than just devices. For mobile teams dealing with financial products, it was key that the solution could deliver high levels of security, alongside the flexibility for salespeople to work safely from anywhere. The ThinkPad\u2019s touchscreens and built-in styluses meant that W&W could keep costs down and reduce the need to carry additional external hardware. Lenovo also helped W&W find a solution that helped its salespeople stay connected on the go, including eSIM functionality for mobile connectivity and remote management of future network upgrades. For additional security, W&W also opted for a Near Field Communication (NFC) reader which could be used to verify customers using ID cards, or for staff to log in using multi-factor authentication. With the devices rolling out to a first wave of 1,400 users with Lenovo\u2019s partner Bechtle, W&W\u2019s experts opted for Lenovo ThinkShield Remote Supervisor Password (RSVP) service, which enables remote management of passwords on a large scale. Linko said, \u201cLenovo understands what is important for us, proactively suggesting features like the new password service to increase device security. The eSIM functionality means we will no longer need to deal with faulty SIM cards and we will be able to change connectivity providers much more easily in the future.\u201d Delivering sustainably Lenovo also considered sustainability impact from shipping through to end-of-life. W&W opted for Lenovo\u2019s Maersk ECO Delivery for many of the devices, using second-generation biofuels to reduce shipping CO2 emissions by more than 80% . The ThinkPad laptops also offer real-time performance reports via Lenovo Device Intelligence (LDI) Plus, an AI-powered Software as a Service (SaaS) PC health management tool which provides detailed device analytics and real-time utilization reports to extend their life. These measures were supplemented by Lenovo CO2 Offset Services , allowing W&W to purchase carbon credits with each device, which support a range of United Nations and Gold Standard\u00ae vetted climate action projects around the world. In addition, Lenovo\u2019s Asset Recovery Services provide secure, documented disposal and recycling of IT hardware when it has reached the end of its useful life. John Stamer, Vice President & General Manager, Global Product Services at Lenovo said : \u201c By optimizing the shipment of ThinkPad devices and collaborating closely with our lab in Bratislava to minimize road miles for testing, our team supported W&W in significantly reducing the carbon footprint of their devices and services. Additionally, Lenovo Device Intelligence Plus enhanced the company\u2019s visibility into device usage, empowering W&W to make informed decisions and drive operational efficiency.\u201d Linko said, \u201cAt our head office, we often use ThinkPad laptops for as long as eight years without issues. With LDI Plus, we can better understand what features are important for our teams and where the bottlenecks are. Using the new metrics and data, we can proactively optimize device configurations and make much better-informed decisions about upgrades and configurations.\u201d Future-ready results The W&W team have high standards for their hardware, and even the most exacting users have been happy with the Lenovo devices. The ThinkPad machines are also ready for future upgrades to NFC-based security, AI workloads and for the move to Windows 11. Lenovo\u2019s software has enabled W&W to manage laptops more intelligently, enabling managers to see how teams are actually using them, offering insights which will be useful for choosing future upgrades. Linko said that the initial rollout has been met with a \u2018very positive\u2019 reaction. He added, \u2018The high-spec configuration gives everyone an impressive performance boost across many complex business applications, increasing staff productivity and satisfaction. Together with Lenovo, we have created a sustainable, future-focused, AI-ready workhorse for our distributed salesforce.\u201d LENOVO and ThinkPad are trademarks of Lenovo. All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners. \u00a92026 Lenovo Learn more about Lenovo\u2019s work with W&W Informatik Learn more about Lenovo CO2 Offset Services Only for Cyprus section No", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:26:12"}}, "385": {"text": "and lessening the environmental impact of its operations. Therefore, it was crucial that the devices used by its mobile sales force were shipped, built and recycled in a way that aligned with W&W\u2019s sustainability strategy. Uli Linko, Head of Client System Technology, at the group\u2019s technology arm W&W Informatik GmbH, said, \u201cWe are always looking for ways to further improve data protection and", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.csr-company.com/node/11545", "title": "Sign on the Dotted Line: Keeping Security and Sustainability in Focus for W&W Informatik Group\u2019s Mobile Sales Force", "description": "With a history stretching back to 1828, and a list of \u2018firsts\u2019 including being the debut German pension insurance and building society, the 16 companies that make up Germany\u2019s Wu\u0308stenrot & Wu\u0308rttembergische (W&W) Informatik Group delivers everything from investment products to risk protection to 6.5 million customers. W&W Informatik Group relies on a highly connected mobile sales force of 8,000 people spread across 2,500 service centers and offices. With contracts increasingly being signed digitally, W&W needed a new device and services strategy to ensure its team had the support required to bring new customers on board. For W&W\u2019s front-line salespeople, it was essential for the devices to be fast and reliable and secure for processing customer data, with security and sustainability also critical business considerations. W&W Informatik Group is committed to a sustainability strategy focused on reducing the company\u2019s carbon footprint and lessening the environmental impact of its operations. Therefore, it was crucial that the devices used by its mobile sales force were shipped, built and recycled in a way that aligned with W&W\u2019s sustainability strategy. Uli Linko, Head of Client System Technology, at the group\u2019s technology arm W&W Informatik GmbH, said, \u201cWe are always looking for ways to further improve data protection and device security. And with AI-supported tools being developed, we needed to equip our sales force with powerful devices that can handle larger amounts of data and more demanding workloads.\u201d W&W had been using Lenovo ThinkPad laptops at its head office for many years and relying on Lenovo server infrastructure. So the team spoke to Lenovo to find the right approach, settling on Lenovo\u2019s \u2018two-in-one\u2019 ThinkPad X13 Yoga Gen 4 laptops, powerful machines which can switch from a laptop mode with a traditional keyboard, to a \u2018tablet mode\u2019 where users can write on screen, perfect for when customers need to sign contracts. To help W&W make its decision, Lenovo was able to provide rapid access to different test devices through its local European lab in Bratislava. Across the lifecycle W&W was looking for more than just devices. For mobile teams dealing with financial products, it was key that the solution could deliver high levels of security, alongside the flexibility for salespeople to work safely from anywhere. The ThinkPad\u2019s touchscreens and built-in styluses meant that W&W could keep costs down and reduce the need to carry additional external hardware. Lenovo also helped W&W find a solution that helped its salespeople stay connected on the go, including eSIM functionality for mobile connectivity and remote management of future network upgrades. For additional security, W&W also opted for a Near Field Communication (NFC) reader which could be used to verify customers using ID cards, or for staff to log in using multi-factor authentication. With the devices rolling out to a first wave of 1,400 users with Lenovo\u2019s partner Bechtle, W&W\u2019s experts opted for Lenovo ThinkShield Remote Supervisor Password (RSVP) service, which enables remote management of passwords on a large scale. Linko said, \u201cLenovo understands what is important for us, proactively suggesting features like the new password service to increase device security. The eSIM functionality means we will no longer need to deal with faulty SIM cards and we will be able to change connectivity providers much more easily in the future.\u201d Delivering sustainably Lenovo also considered sustainability impact from shipping through to end-of-life. W&W opted for Lenovo\u2019s Maersk ECO Delivery for many of the devices, using second-generation biofuels to reduce shipping CO2 emissions by more than 80% . The ThinkPad laptops also offer real-time performance reports via Lenovo Device Intelligence (LDI) Plus, an AI-powered Software as a Service (SaaS) PC health management tool which provides detailed device analytics and real-time utilization reports to extend their life. These measures were supplemented by Lenovo CO2 Offset Services , allowing W&W to purchase carbon credits with each device, which support a range of United Nations and Gold Standard\u00ae vetted climate action projects around the world. In addition, Lenovo\u2019s Asset Recovery Services provide secure, documented disposal and recycling of IT hardware when it has reached the end of its useful life. John Stamer, Vice President & General Manager, Global Product Services at Lenovo said : \u201c By optimizing the shipment of ThinkPad devices and collaborating closely with our lab in Bratislava to minimize road miles for testing, our team supported W&W in significantly reducing the carbon footprint of their devices and services. Additionally, Lenovo Device Intelligence Plus enhanced the company\u2019s visibility into device usage, empowering W&W to make informed decisions and drive operational efficiency.\u201d Linko said, \u201cAt our head office, we often use ThinkPad laptops for as long as eight years without issues. With LDI Plus, we can better understand what features are important for our teams and where the bottlenecks are. Using the new metrics and data, we can proactively optimize device configurations and make much better-informed decisions about upgrades and configurations.\u201d Future-ready results The W&W team have high standards for their hardware, and even the most exacting users have been happy with the Lenovo devices. The ThinkPad machines are also ready for future upgrades to NFC-based security, AI workloads and for the move to Windows 11. Lenovo\u2019s software has enabled W&W to manage laptops more intelligently, enabling managers to see how teams are actually using them, offering insights which will be useful for choosing future upgrades. Linko said that the initial rollout has been met with a \u2018very positive\u2019 reaction. He added, \u2018The high-spec configuration gives everyone an impressive performance boost across many complex business applications, increasing staff productivity and satisfaction. Together with Lenovo, we have created a sustainable, future-focused, AI-ready workhorse for our distributed salesforce.\u201d LENOVO and ThinkPad are trademarks of Lenovo. All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners. \u00a92026 Lenovo Learn more about Lenovo\u2019s work with W&W Informatik Learn more about Lenovo CO2 Offset Services Only for Cyprus section No", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 03:26:12"}}, "386": {"text": "for ways to further improve data protection and device security. And with AI-supported tools being developed, we n