n the SME economy will bring together business owners, policymakers, and ecosystem leaders to explore trends shaping small business growth today. Sessions throughout the day will shine a spotlight on female entrepreneurship, market access, customer expansion, and the challenges of building sustainable brands in a competitive environment. The summit will conclude with an SME exhibition, showcasing innovative products, solutions, and tools designed to support enterprise growth. This will provide attendees with practical opportunities to engage, network, and explore collaborations that can take their businesses to the next level. Shaping the Future Together As the summit approaches, business leaders, entrepreneurs, and visionaries are encouraged to seize the opportunity to connect, learn, and build. The Nigeria Business Summit is more than a platform for listening\u2014it is a space for meaningful collaboration, problem-solving, and engagement with leaders actively shaping the trajectory of Nigeria\u2019s business economy. Registration is now open. For more information and to secure your place at the summit, visit www.stanbicibtc.com . This is where ideas will spark, partnerships will form, and the future of Nigeria\u2019s business landscape will be reimagined.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 21:34:00"}}, "599": {"text": "and charting pathways to advance Nigerian businesses in their journey toward sustainable growth and international competitiveness. A Gathering of Visionaries The summit\u2019s theme, \u201cNigeria Means Business: Powering Sectors, Growing Sustainable SMEs & Unlocking Global Trade,\u201d reflects a commitment to nurturing business growth from multiple perspectives. Across the two days, participants will engage", "metadata": {"source": "http://www.brandiconimage.com/2026/03/stanbic-ibtc-hosts-nigeria-business.html", "title": "Stanbic IBTC Hosts Nigeria Business Summit to Support Sustainable Business, Sector Development", "description": "In a world that oft