onaries are encouraged to seize the opportunity to connect, learn, and build. The Nigeria Business Summit is more than a platform for listening\u2014it is a space for meaningful collaboration, problem-solving, and engagement with leaders actively shaping the trajectory of Nigeria\u2019s business economy. Registration is now open. For more information and to secure your place at the summit, visit www.stanbicibtc.com . This is where ideas will spark, partnerships will form, and the future of Nigeria\u2019s business landscape will be reimagined.", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 21:34:00"}}, "609": {"text": "BlackBerry-style phone gets aluminum body and AMOLED display upgrade. Shanghai-based Unihertz has made a name for itself in recent years with its varied lineup of rugged phones, tiny phones, and BlackBerry-style handsets with full physical keyboards. Continue Reading Category: Mobile Technology , Consumer Tech , Technology Tags: Phone , Unihertz , Keyboard , MWC 2026 , Kickstarter ONLY AVAILABLE", "metadata": {"source": "https://newatlas.com/mobile-technology/unihertz-qwerty-keyboard-phone-titan2-elite/", "title": "BlackBerry-style phone gets aluminum body and AMOLED display upgrade", "description": "Shanghai-based Unihertz has made a name for itself in recent years with its varied lineup of rugged phones, tiny phones, and BlackBerry-style handsets with full physical keyboards. Continue Reading Category: Mobile Technology , Consumer Tech , Technology Tags: Phone , Unihertz , Keyboard , MWC 2026 , Kickstarter", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:03:00"}}, "610": {"text": "Keyboard , MWC 2026 , Kickstarter ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://newatlas.com/mobile-technology/unihertz-qwerty-keyboard-phone-titan2-elite/", "title": "BlackBerry-style phone gets aluminum body and AMOLED display upgrade", "description": "Shanghai-based Unihertz has made a name for itself in recent years with its varied lineup of rugged phones, tiny phones, and BlackBerry-style handsets with full physical keyboards. Continue Reading Category: Mobile Technology , Consumer Tech , Technology Tags: Phone , Unihertz , Keyboard , MWC 2026 , Kickstarter", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:03:00"}}, "611": {"text": "Selective enforcement \u2013 Who guards the guardians?. I WRITE today out of a deep sense of unease, not merely at isolated acts of alleged misconduct, but at the growing perception that key institutions are being bent, if not weaponised, in ways that threaten both the rule of law and the integrity of governance under the Madani administration led by Anwar Ibrahim. Corporate [...] The post Selective", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.theborneopost.com/2026/03/29/selective-enforcement-who-guards-the-guardians/", "title": "Selective enforcement \u2013 Who guards the guardians?", "description": "I WRITE today out of a deep sense of unease, not merely at isolated acts of alleged misconduct, but at the growing perception that key institutions are being bent, if not weaponised, in ways that threaten both the rule of law and the integrity of governance under the Madani administration led by Anwar Ibrahim. Corporate [...] The post Selective enforcement \u2013 Who guards the guardians? appeared first on Borneo Post Online .", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:02:41"}}, "612": {"text": "Anwar Ibrahim. Corporate [...] The post Selective enforcement \u2013 Who guards the guardians? appeared first on Borneo Post Online . ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.theborneopost.com/2026/03/29/selective-enforcement-who-guards-the-guardians/", "title": "Selective enforcement \u2013 Who guards the guardians?", "description": "I WRITE today out of a deep sense of unease, not merely at isolated acts of alleged misconduct, but at the growing perception that key institutions are being bent, if not weaponised, in ways that threaten both the rule of law and the integrity of governance under the Madani administration led by Anwar Ibrahim. Corporate [...] The post Selective enforcement \u2013 Who guards the guardians? appeared first on Borneo Post Online .", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:02:41"}}, "613": {"text": "Breaking the Habit?. The latest staff-level agreement with the IMF deserves to be read in Pakistan as a welcome signal, despite what social media warriors and propagandists\u2019 accounts operating across the border would have one believe. Once approved by the Fund\u2019s board, it would release about $1.2 billion under the Extended Fund Facility and another $210 million under [...] ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID", "metadata": {"source": "https://dailytimes.com.pk/1470155/breaking-the-habit/", "title": "Breaking the Habit?", "description": "The latest staff-level agreement with the IMF deserves to be read in Pakistan as a welcome signal, despite what social media warriors and propagandists\u2019 accounts operating across the border would have one believe. Once approved by the Fund\u2019s board, it would release about $1.2 billion under the Extended Fund Facility and another $210 million under [...]", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:01:44"}}, "614": {"text": "$210 million under [...] ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://dailytimes.com.pk/1470155/breaking-the-habit/", "title": "Breaking the Habit?", "description": "The latest staff-level agreement with the IMF deserves to be read in Pakistan as a welcome signal, despite what social media warriors and propagandists\u2019 accounts operating across the border would have one believe. Once approved by the Fund\u2019s board, it would release about $1.2 billion under the Extended Fund Facility and another $210 million under [...]", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:01:44"}}, "615": {"text": "The politics of petroleum. WHILE the war in the Middle East over the control of oil is raging, here in our little corner of the world, we Malaysians are fighting among ourselves, also over the same kind of mineral. The battle ground is the courtroom. Petronas is challenging the competency of the Sarawak State Legislative Assembly (DUN) to enact [...] The post The politics of petroleum appeared", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.theborneopost.com/2026/03/29/the-politics-of-petroleum/", "title": "The politics of petroleum", "description": "WHILE the war in the Middle East over the control of oil is raging, here in our little corner of the world, we Malaysians are fighting among ourselves, also over the same kind of mineral. The battle ground is the courtroom. Petronas is challenging the competency of the Sarawak State Legislative Assembly (DUN) to enact [...] The post The politics of petroleum appeared first on Borneo Post Online .", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:01:24"}}, "616": {"text": "[...] The post The politics of petroleum appeared first on Borneo Post Online . ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.theborneopost.com/2026/03/29/the-politics-of-petroleum/", "title": "The politics of petroleum", "description": "WHILE the war in the Middle East over the control of oil is raging, here in our little corner of the world, we Malaysians are fighting among ourselves, also over the same kind of mineral. The battle ground is the courtroom. Petronas is challenging the competency of the Sarawak State Legislative Assembly (DUN) to enact [...] The post The politics of petroleum appeared first on Borneo Post Online .", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:01:24"}}, "617": {"text": "Beads of love and legacy. IN a quiet corner of her home in Miri, trays of shimmering beads catch the soft light from a desk lamp. Carefully arranged by colour and size, they wait patiently beside neatly folded fabrics. Seated at the table, Rudang Balang works with steady hands, threading bead after bead into intricate patterns that have been passed [...] The post Beads of love and legacy appeared", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.theborneopost.com/2026/03/29/beads-of-love-and-legacy/", "title": "Beads of love and legacy", "description": "IN a quiet corner of her home in Miri, trays of shimmering beads catch the soft light from a desk lamp. Carefully arranged by colour and size, they wait patiently beside neatly folded fabrics. Seated at the table, Rudang Balang works with steady hands, threading bead after bead into intricate patterns that have been passed [...] The post Beads of love and legacy appeared first on Borneo Post Online .", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:00:56"}}, "618": {"text": "[...] The post Beads of love and legacy appeared first on Borneo Post Online . ONLY AVAILABLE IN PAID PLANS", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.theborneopost.com/2026/03/29/beads-of-love-and-legacy/", "title": "Beads of love and legacy", "description": "IN a quiet corner of her home in Miri, trays of shimmering beads catch the soft light from a desk lamp. Carefully arranged by colour and size, they wait patiently beside neatly folded fabrics. Seated at the table, Rudang Balang works with steady hands, threading bead after bead into intricate patterns that have been passed [...] The post Beads of love and legacy appeared first on Borneo Post Online .", "publishedAt": "2026-03-28 22:00:56"}}, "619": {"text": "25 years on, Boao forum provides reassuring voice amid global instability, uncertainty. HAINAN (March 29): As the humid spring breeze drifts in from the South China Sea, Boao, a tranquil town on China\u2019s tropical island of Hainan, once again draws global attention. The 2026 annual conference of the Boao Forum for Asia (BFA) is being held here from March 24 to 27 under the theme \u201cShaping a [...] The", "metadata": {"source": "https://www.theborneopost.com/2026/03/29/25-years-on-boao-forum-provides-reassuring-voice-amid-global-instability-uncertainty/", "title": "25 years on, Boao forum provides reassuring voice amid global instability, uncertainty", "description": "HAINAN (March 29): As the humid spring breeze drifts in from the South China Sea, Boao, a tranquil town on China\u